cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with a game played on a geometric board, where players place points and try to win the most area. This involves concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG), such as Voronoi diagrams, as well as algorithms and complexity theory (cs.DS, cs.CC) for analyzing the game and determining optimal strategies. The paper also involves combinatorics (cs.DM) in characterizing the outcome of the game for different parameter values, and game theory (cs.GT) in analyzing the strategies of the players.
